# Astro Development Guidelines

## Astro Component Best Practices

- Use proper TypeScript types for component props
- Keep client-side scripts minimal and focused
- Use Astro's built-in Image component for optimized images
- Prefer server-side rendering when possible

## Search Feature Implementation

The search functionality in [src/pages/index.astro](mdc:src/pages/index.astro) includes:

- Real-time filtering with `input` event listeners
- TypeScript type assertions for DOM elements
- Proper null checks and error handling
- Data attributes for searchable content

## Code Style

- Use proper TypeScript type assertions: `as HTMLInputElement`
- Include null checks: `if (!element) return;`
- Use descriptive variable names
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose

## Performance Considerations

- Use `loading="lazy"` for images below the fold
- Minimize client-side JavaScript
- Leverage Astro's static generation capabilities
- Use CSS classes for styling instead of inline styles
